item.title: Coronavirus Has Indians Selling the Family Gold
item.description: Investors across the globe are hoarding gold in the Covid-19 pandemic. In normally gold-obsessed India, there’s a glut, as struggling families stop buying and start hocking jewelry.

item.title: Russian Fighter Planes Confronted U.S. Bomber Over Black Sea
item.description: Russian pilots harassed a U.S. B-52 bomber flying in the region, crossing within 100 feet of the American aircraft’s path in a maneuver the U.S. military called unsafe and unprofessional.

item.title: Baath Party Archives, and the Secrets They Contain, Return to Iraq
item.description: A U.S. military cargo plane stuffed with documents that hold the secrets of Iraq’s dictatorial past, including the names of Baath Party members and informants, landed at the Baghdad airport Monday.

item.title: Turkish Economy Weakens, Posing Challenge for Erdogan
item.description: A sharp economic contraction in Turkey threatens President Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s pledge to rapidly revive the nation’s economic prosperity.

item.title: In France, the Young Lose Their Jobs to Coronavirus
item.description: Young workers, having suffered from chronically high unemployment in France for more than a decade, are now bearing the brunt of the economic fallout from the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Israeli Flight Lands in U.A.E. to Mark New Diplomatic Era
item.description: The first direct commercial flight from Tel Aviv arrived in the United Arab Emirates, carrying top Israeli and U.S. officials who marked a tangible step toward a new era of diplomatic ties between the two countries.
